                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 125.8273/62.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister at Mexico
                            City</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Very happy to advise Department that Vice Consul Silliman reached this city
                    this morning early and is at this moment in the Legation. He made his trip to
                    this city accompanied by a representative of the British Vice Consul at Saltillo
                    and will leave tomorrow for the States via Vera Cruz duly protected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
